import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Distances')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of distances between airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    country_airport_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    country_airport_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('Which country has the highest number of airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude of airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='country', y='distance', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport distances within a country?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Distance')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Country', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
